5:
Wow, look at the selection they've
got here!
8:
Organic life-forms, in the flesh? 
I thought you were just a rumor.
10:
Not only do you exist, you even
came to my shop.
13:
Is this a gun, too? I can't see a
trigger anywhere... 
How does it even fire?!
17:
Excuse me, I'd like to see some other
guns. Do you have any
recommendations?
20:
Of course. I'd like you to show me
your gun first, though.
26:
...You're really using an antique like
this in combat?
31:
It's time to trade up. This one's pretty
nice, don't you think?
33:
It's an automatic sniper rifle with
integrated target-tracking.
Essentially, it aims itself.
34:
Compared to your weapon, its
range and precision are simply on
another level.
40:
It's a deal, then. I'll even throw in
some ammo, free of charge.
44:
W-wait a minute! You've got
something special there, sure, but
I'm not about to buy it!
47:
Why? Compare the specs and it's an
easy choice.
50:
Forget specs! This old gal and I have
seen it all together!
53:
I couldn't just toss her aside like
that...
56:
I see. I've got a shooting range in the
back, so let me show you what this
gun is capable of.
67: So you're a good shot, then.
70:
No, the gun did that itself. It boasts
capabilities that your weapon
simply cannot compete with.
71:
Well? It's time to trade up, don't you
think?
74:
I'll admit you made quick work of
those targets. But if that's all you
can do...
78: I'm afraid she and I can do the same.
80:
I like that attitude, but... Maybe this
will finally convince you. Simulator!
84:
S-surely you aren't going to shoot
through such violent winds!
87:
Why not? These conditions pose no
problem for this gun.
89:
Now this is more like it! It's quite like
being out in the field!
93:
Uh... Why is she suddenly super into
this?
100:
What do you think? Surely you can't
compete with that.
103:
WHAT?! How did you calculate such
a shot under those conditions?!
104:
That... That shouldn't be possible!
Not without illegal nerve tuning, or
107:
I've known nothing but the ocean
since I was little. Me and my gal are
more than used to rough waves and
harsh winds...
110:
We could shoot through all that with
our eyes closed.
112:
We could shoot through all that with
our eyes closed.
114:
I think I'm starting to understand
why you're so attached to that
weapon.
119:
That went well, eh? Hard to say no to
a free tune-up.
122:
I'll say. She shoots just a little
straighter now.
124:
Maybe I should keep going there for
maintenance in the future...
128:
You might want to be careful with
that. I don't think that clerk has given
up trying to sell you a gun.
132:
Merchants are always looking to get
rid of their goods. Doesn't matter
what world you're in.
137:
Don't worry yourselves. I won't be
giving my gal up anytime soon.
141:
The gun back at the shop seemed
solid, but Evelyn's is pretty
irreplaceable.
145:
Yes. The two of them make a great
team.
150:
Hehe! I'm itching to see the results of
the tune-up, so let's hop worlds and
hurry back!
